{
  "text": "Cluster 2 comprised younger, more recently graduated dentists (Table 4) , and consequently includes the majority of those who only have a graduate degree (74.2%) and general practitioners (93.3%). Another relevant fact is that professionals in this group work in small or medium-sized municipalities (46.0%), suggesting a tendency towards moving to a country town to exercise the profession, which occurs principally because of work opportunities. The positive views of the profession of this group were also observed by Baldwin et al. [CITATION_1] , who concluded that very young dentists tend to have a very positive attitude towards their work and career.",
